No worries, it's rough out here when there aren't easily accessible "standard practices" floating around. Everything I do now has been picked up from other artists kind enough to share some tips on their process publicly 😔

Typically, for private commissions I only give out the PSD if requested, and I charge extra for it. When I send out the "final files," it includes a high-resolution version and a web-resolution version (PNG, PDF, or TIF, based on client preference), both with my signature present.
Also everything I post gets flagged as sensitive 😆
